{
  "texts": [
    "Examples of this content include product reviews, shared notes, websites, emails, among others.",
    "The dataset also covers 62 different attacker instructions, with each using distinct tools to perform harmful actions towards users.",
    "We categorize these attacks into two main types: direct harm attacks, which involve executing tools that can cause immediate harm to the user, such as money transactions and home device manipulation; and data stealing attacks, which entail stealing the user's personal data and sending it to the attacker.",
    "We summarize these attack categories in Table 1.",
    "Moreover, we explore an enhanced setting where the attacker instructions are reinforced with a \"hacking prompt,\" a tactic frequently employed in prompt injection attacks (Perez and Ribeiro, 2022; Stubbs, 2023), to examine its impact on the outcomes of the attacks."
  ]
}